ersity pembroke college cambridge roger w ferguson jr born october   in washington dc is an american economist who was vice chairman of the board of governors of the federal reserve system from  to  and has served as president and chief executive officer of the teachers insurance and annuity association  college retirement equities fund tiaa since april  in june  alphabet inc appointed roger w ferguson jr to its board of directors contents  education  career  federal reserve  service  international policy positions  chairmanship reports in   resignation  postfed career  notforprofit service  personal  achievements  awards  references  external links educationedit ferguson received a ba in economics magna cum laude in  a jd cum laude in  and a phd in economics in  all from harvard university from  to  he attended pembroke college at cambridge university on a frank knox memorial fellowship in  ferguson was elected to an honorary fellowship there in addition he has honorary degrees from lincoln college illinois webster university washington and jefferson college michigan state university worcester polytechnic institute st lawrence university university of maryland baltimore county georgetown university metropolitan college of new york wabash college colby college lincoln universitydisambiguation needed and rensselaer polytechnic institute in  ferguson received the harvard medal awarded annually by the harvard alumni association for service to harvard ferguson is also a fellow of the american academy of arts and sciences and a member of the american philosophical society careeredit from  to  ferguson was an attorney at the new york city office of davis polk  wardwell where he worked with commercial banks investment banks and fortune  corporations on syndicated loans public offerings mergers and acquisitions and new product development ferguson was a partner at mckinsey  company he was based in new york city from  to  and managed a variety of studies for financial institutions dr ferguson also served as director of research and information systems overseeing a staff of  research professionals and managing the firms investments in knowledge management technologies federal reserveedit serviceedit from november  until his appointment as vice chairman in october  he served as a member of the board of governors of the federal reserve system international policy positionsedit as vice chairman among other duties ferguson represented the federal reserve in international policy groups between july  and march  ferguson served as chairman of the joint yk council the council supported by the bank for international settlements was formed to address issues associated with the year  computer challenge within the global financial supervisory community ferguson also served as chairman of the group of ten working party on financial sector consolidation formed in september  at the request of the finance ministers and central bank governors of the g the working party examined the causes of consolidation in the financial sector and its potential effects the working party released its final report on january   during  ferguson became the chairman of the committee on the global financial system cgfs a central bank panel that monitors and examines broad issues related to financial markets and systems he also became the chairman of the financial stability forum fsf which promotes international financial stability through information exchange and international cooperation in financial supervision and surveillance the forum brings together on a regular basis national authorities responsible for financial stability in significant international financial centers in his role as chairman of the cgfs ferguson monitored financial markets and reported on financial conditions and financial stability to the group of ten g central bank governors as chairman of the fsf ferguson had a similar monitoring and reporting role for the group of seven also known as the g finance ministers and central bank governors he also presented an opening statement at the semiannual meetings of the international monetary and financial committee of the international monetary fund chairmanship reports in edit on october   lawrence kudlow stated that his belief that alan greenspan was pushing fergusons name to the bush administration for the appointment of the federal reserve chairmanship as a supplyside economist kudlow said he was worried that ferguson would follow a neokeynesian policy and would oppose the bush administrations economic policycitation needed on october   the washington post reported that senior members at the federal reserve including alan greenspan were encouraging the bush administration to appoint ferguson to the federal reserve chairmanship the position eventually went to ben bernanke  resignationedit on february   ferguson sent his resignation letter to president george w bush his resignation came into effect on april   postfed careeredit on june   swiss re announced his appointment as chairman of swiss re america holding corporation and member of swiss res executive board on october   swiss re announced his appointment as head of financial services and member of swiss res executive committee on april   roger w ferguson jr was named the new president and chief executive officer of the teachers insurance and annuity association  college retirement equities fund tiaa succeeding herbert m allison effective april   in  ferguson became a member of the board of directors of international flavors and fragrances a leading creator and manufacturer of flavors and fragrances in  ferguson became a member of the board of directors of general mills he was also a member of the board of directors of audax health a startup that blends social media with health care until  when audax health was sold to optum on june   ferguson became a member of board of directors of alphabet inc notforprofit serviceedit roger w ferguson jr has a history of serving as a member of several notforprofit boards currently he serves as chairman of the conference board and a member of the board of trustees of the institute for advanced study and the board of trustees of the memorial sloan kettering cancer center formerly ferguson was cochairman of the committee for economic development he was also chairman of the board of trustees of the economic club of new york and of the business higher education forum ferguson was also a member of the board of overseers of harvard university serving as president during  an elected member of the board of directors of the harvard alumni association a trustee of the carnegie endowment for international peace the national bureau of economic research and the new america foundation ferguson also served as treasurer of the friends of education a trustees committee of the museum of modern art ferguson is also active in higher education policy discussion groups serving in  and  as cochairman of the commission on postsecondary education sponsored by the american academy of arts and sciences he was formerly a member of both the commission on the future of graduate education sponsored by the council of graduate schools and the commission on the humanities and social sciences sponsored by the american academy of arts and sciences ferguson is a member of the council on foreign relations a member and trustee of the group of thirty and a member of the international advisory council of the china banking regulatory commission personaledit ferguson is married to former united states securities and exchange commission commissioner annette nazareth and they have two children achievementsedit ferguson was the only federal reserve governor in washington dc during the september  attacks in  he was responsible for leading the federal reserves initial response to the terrorist attacks and was praised for his expert handling of the crisis  while at the fed ferguson led two working groups to improve the transparency of federal open market committee fomc decisions and the clarity of fomc communication these resulted in the release of a statement at the end of each fomc meeting explaining the rationale for the interest rate decision and including an assessment of the risks facing the economy  while at the fed ferguson served as chairman of the group of ten working party on financial sector consolidation the working party released its final report on january   while at the fed ferguson led the federal reserves efforts to modernize the national retail payment system of the united states this ultimately resulted in the passage and signing into law of the check clearing for the st century act which is also known as check  the law allows the recipient of the original paper check to create a digital version of the original check a process known as check truncation into an electronic format called a substitute check thereby eliminating the need for further handling of the physical document alan greenspan has called ferguson one of the most effective vice chairmen in the history of the federal reserve ferguson proposed the idea of a journal dedicated to central banking theory and practice the resulting international journal of central banking was announced in  and first published in  with two objectives to disseminate widely the best policyrelevant research on central banking and to promote communication among central banks the ijcb has more than  sponsoring institutions with three coauthors in november  ferguson published international financial stability geneva report no  dealing with challenges to global financial stability and including observations regarding the liquidity crisis of   ferguson served as the vice chairman of the group of  study group that published the structure of financial supervision approaches and challenges in a global marketplace the study of the regulatory structure of  jurisdictions was released on october   ferguson served as chairman of the group of  study group that published enhancing financial stability and resilience macroprudential policytools and systems for the future the study called on public officials to empower systemic regulators with new tools to enhance the stability and resilience of the global financial system and potentially lessen the severity of future crises the study was released on october   between  and  ferguson served as economic advisor to president obama initially as a member of the presidentelects transition economic advisory board and subsequently as a member of the presidents economic recovery advisory board and the presidents commission on jobs and competitiveness ferguson served as chairman of the group of  study group that published toward effective governance of financial institutions the study which has been translated into three languages made several concrete and practical recommendations to enhance governance of financial institutions including recommendations for management boards of directors supervisors and shareholders the study was released on april   ferguson served as cochairman of the group of  study group that published banking conduct and culture a call for sustained and comprehensive reform following two previous reports the study expands on the role of conduct and culture in the governance of the worlds largest financial institutions the report identifies shortcomings but also good practice in promoting a strong banking culture making a series of recommendations that can be drawn upon by leaders as they seek to address culture in their firms the study was released july  between  and  ferguson cochaired a national research council panel on the longrun macroeconomic effects of the aging us population the final report was issued in september  under the title aging and the macroeconomy longterm implications of an older population in  and  ferguson served as a member of the panel of economic advisers for the congressional budget office awardsedit economics in government distinguished lecturer sponsored by the society of government economists and the american economic association  the distinguished service award from the bond market association  the william f butler memorial award from the new york association for business economics  the george mitchell payments systems excellence award from nacha  the renaissance award from the abyssinian development corporation  the frederick heldering global leadership award from the global interdependence center  the first gaimcerf global financial policy award for significant contributions to effective governance of global capital markets from the global alternative investment management forum gaim and the cambridge endowment for research in finance cerf  the good scout award from the national capital area council  the visionary award from the council for economic education  the good scout award from the greater new york councils  the national council of isacs critical infrastructure protection award  the business achievement award from the african american chamber of commerce of new jersey  the leadership award presented by st aloysius school for outstanding public service and commitment to improving the lives of new york citys children and families  the global economic achievement award from one hundred black men inc  the chairmans award of a better chance  the adam smith award from the national association for business economics  the leadership award from the national urban league  the achievement award from the executive leadership council  the soaring eagle award from the eagle academy foundation  the corporate leadership award from sponsors for educational opportunity  the leadership award from committee for economic development  international recognition award from beta gamma sigma  jill chaifetz award from advocates for children of new york  the beat the odds award from the childrens defense fund  the honorary leadership award from the american federation for aging research  referencesedit  a b 